      <!-- Club Mania (1st Semester) -->
      <div class="event">
          <h3>General Rules :-</h3>
          <p>
             All the participants must come on time .<br>
             Only one sheet is gonna provide you so please use the sheet carefully.<br>
             Work must be original.<br>
             Don’t use phones while competition.<br>
             Write your details on an corner of your work .
          </p>
          <h3>Specific Guidelines :-</h3>
          <p>
             Limit your text, small sentences, simple words and bullets to illustrate your topic.<br>
             Choose an image or two that portrays your message well. Images should be able to capture attention and also relate to the purpose of the poster.<br>
             Use no more than two font types and only three or four font sizes. For instance, the headline should be the largest, while the benefits should be a smaller size.<br>
             Don't go overboard on color. The background should be a muted color or should contrast the text color.<br>
             When it comes to the layout, leave lots of space. Control the eye flow by grouping information logically and using space to draw the viewer's attention through the layout.<br>
             Design more than one layout. Try different colors, fonts, and sizes to make the poster more creative and attractive.
          </p>
          <h3>Judging Criteria :-</h3>
          <p>
             Originality & Creativity (20-30%)<br>
             Relevance to the Theme (20-30%))<br>
             Visual Impact (20-25%)<br>
             Technical Skill (15-20%)<br>
             Content and Accuracy (10-15%)
          </p>
          <h3>Disqualification Condition :-</h3>
          <p>
             Failing to adhere to the specified theme or topic of the competition.<br>
             Using banned tools, mediums, or techniques, such as digital elements in a competition restricted to hand-drawn posters.<br>
             Inclusion of hazardous materials or items not allowed by the organizers.<br>
             Copying designs, images, or content from other sources without originality.<br>
             Submitting the poster after the deadline or failing to complete it within the allotted time during live events.<br>
             Ignoring specific instructions, such as mandatory inclusion of logos, slogans, or particular design elements.<br>
             Tampering with others' work, displaying inappropriate behavior, or violating the competition's code of conduct.
          </p>
      </div>
